  "prompt": "What can you buy with 4.95 canadian dollars on the Internet that's worth it?",
  "response": "With 4.95 Canadian dollars, you can find various digital products or services online. Here are some options that might be worth considering:\n\n1. **E-books**: Many authors offer their short stories or novellas for prices around this range. Look for promotions or self-published works.\n\n2. **Mobile Apps/Games**: Some mobile applications or indie games may cost around $4.95. Check platforms like the App Store or Google Play Store for deals.\n\n3. **Digital Music**: Purchase a single or two tracks from platforms like Bandcamp or iTunes. \n\n4. **Subscription Services**: You might find a promotional offer for a month of subscription services like streaming platforms or online magazines.\n\n5. **Online Courses**: Some platforms offer snippets or introductory content for low prices, perfect for exploring new topics.\n\n6. **Art or Graphics**: Digital downloads from artists on sites like Etsy or Creative Market can sometimes be found for this price.\n\n7. **Printable Designs**: Look for planners, wall art, or other printable items on Etsy.\n\n8. **Charitable Donations**: If you're feeling generous, donating this amount to a charity or crowdfunding campaign can also be worthwhile.\n\nAlways check reviews and product details to ensure you\u2019re getting something valuable for your money!",
